TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;
$a=random(1,10,1);
$b=random(1,10,1)*random(-1,1,2);
$c=random(1,10,1)*random(-1,1,2);

BEGIN_TEXT

$PAR
Consider the function \(f(x)=e^{-x^2},\;-2 \le x \le 2.\)

$PAR
(a) Estimate the area under the graph of \(f\) using four approximating rectangles and taking the sample points to be right endpoints.  Include at least six decimal places in your answers.

$PAR
\(R_{4} = \) \{ans_rule(40)\}

$PAR
(b) Repeat part (a), with midpoints as the sample points.  Include at least six decimal places in your answers.

$PAR
\(M_{4} = \) \{ans_rule(40)\}

$PAR
(c) Now estimate the area under the graph of \(f\) using eight approximating rectangles and taking the sample points to be right endpoints.  Include at least six decimal places in your answers.

$PAR
\(R_{8} = \) \{ans_rule(40)\}

$PAR
(d) Repeat part (c), with midpoints as the sample points.  Include at least six decimal places in your answers.

$PAR
\(M_{8} = \) \{ans_rule(40)\}

END_TEXT

ANS(num_cmp("exp(-1)+exp(0)+exp(-1)+exp(-4)", reltol=>0.001));
ANS(num_cmp("exp(-9/4)+exp(-1/4)+exp(-1/4)+exp(-9/4)", reltol=>0.001));
ANS(num_cmp("0.5*(exp(-9/4)+exp(-1)+exp(-1/4)+exp(0)+exp(-1/4)+exp(-1)+exp(-9/4)+exp(-4))", reltol=>0.001));
ANS(num_cmp("0.5*(exp(-49/16)+exp(-25/16)+exp(-9/16)+exp(-1/16)+exp(-1/16)+exp(-9/16)+exp(-25/16)+exp(-49/16))", reltol=>0.001));

